<subSubSection pageId="156" pageNumber="758" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="156.[2062,2655,372,800]" pageId="156" pageNumber="758">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2062,2343,648,682]" pageId="156" pageNumber="758">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 155- 200 mm, tail 166-194 mm, ear 21-25 mm, hindfoot 32-35 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Silinda
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="156.[1446,2654,808,1311]" pageId="156" pageNumber="758">Rock Rat is a large-sized rat with fur coarse and buffy brown to dark brown dorsally and pale gray ventrally. Ears are medium-sized and brown. Tail is long (103-110% of head-body length) and coarsely scaled with fine hairs, brownish above and paler below. Limbs are relatively short, the foreand hindfeet dorsally yellowish-brown, with four digits on forefoot and five on hindfoot.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
